   without first obtaining written permission from RBF Software.

   It is for the purchasers' use only and as such may be printed out for
   that purpose only, it may not be passed on to other bodies.

   PIRATES..You are killing the Amiga...does it make you feel proud? :-((

@ENDNODE

@NODE o_v500b "OctaMED Professional V5.00b"
** OctaMED Professional V5.00b (04 Jul 1993) ***Copyright RBF Software***

This revision fixes many bugs found in V5.00:

a) The following features unconverted from version 4 have been dealt with:

   * Loading a new sample list (menu item in the Sample List Editor)
   * Sample list statistics (again a menu item in the Sample List Editor)
   * Keyboard shortcuts: Left Amiga-Space (Play Block), Shift-Alt-X/C/V
     (Cut/Copy/Paste Block), Ctrl-T and Shift-Ctrl-T (Create Pitch Slide)

b) Synth editor: when dragging the Length slider, the waveform display is
   now only updated when the length slider has been released (quicker).
   Also in the Pixel Density window (Sample Editor), the display is only
   updated when the slider is released.

c) Opening the Functions window (Input Map Editor) now correctly moves the
   scroll bar to its position when the window was last closed.

d) Some functions which use file requesters no longer go haywire when the
   user specifies a blank filename and tries to save the files: Save
   Settings, Save Instrument, Save Keys, Save Msg, and Save Map.

e) Playing Sequence: clicking New Sec Here now updates the playing sequence
   list correctly.

f) Pressing Delete in the section list updates the numerical box correctly
   to show the new section number highlighted by the white bar.

g) Clicking a new directory in the Instrument Load Window now moves the
   instrument list to the very top instead of retaining the old position.

h) If a Hold value for an instrument is set to anything other than zero,
   entering notes with that instrument and with spacing on no longer cuts
   the note a split second after it is played. (Also occured in V4)

i) Right Alt-F correctly inserts the Right Alt programmable key definition
   with the default pitch.

j) If a sample has just been played and the Sample Editor window is then
   opened, the white cursor no longer scrolls across the waveform.

k) A few of the new keyboard shortcuts used to perform an additional action
   to the one they were intended to. They have been fixed, and were:

      i) Ctrl-G (also joined blocks)
     ii) Ctrl-J (also killed notes to the end of the current track)
    iii) (Shift)-Ctrl-B (also appened a new block)
     iv) (Shift)-Ctrl-S (also deleted a block)

l) The "FourBitPalette" setting is now correctly saved as well as loaded.

m) Confirmation message: "Deleted." is now displayed after file deletion.
@ENDNODE

@NODE o_v500c "OctaMED Professional V5.00c"
** OctaMED Professional V5.00c (11 Jul 1993) ***Copyright RBF Software***

A few more bugs fixed:

a) Accidentally clicking the sample editor waveform when no sample is
   loaded no longer gurus (#8000 0003) under 68000 processors.

b) Redirecting print to a file (Print Options) now checks to see if the
   file already exists, and displays an "Overwrite?" requester if so.

c) Save Options: the "Buffer written. File size xxxxx bytes" and "Module
   saved" messages were never seen in previous versions, because they were
   displayed BEFORE the window was closed instead of AFTER (which is the
   new operation).

d) The print header (Print Options) has had a slight clean-up:

      i) Hold, Dec and Mpr now show all possible digits
     ii) The layout is a bit tidier (line feeds added etc.)

e) Confirmation message: "Printed." is now displayed after printing. This
   was quite necessary, because the user could get the impression
   (especially when printing to a file) that printing was still continuing
   when it had in fact stopped.

f) Ctrl-NM( (Previous Song) and Shift-Ctrl-NM( (Delete Last Song) now work.
@ENDNODE

@NODE o_v500d "OctaMED Professional V5.00d"
** OctaMED Professional V5.00d (01 Aug 1993) ***Copyright RBF Software***

Another bug-fix release (with a few minor additions):

a) The RBF Software image has been added to the About requester.

b) Pressing Del with Space and Chord on advances the correct number of
   lines (it previously only advanced one line). (Also occurred in V4)

c) The Play Block shortcut is now Right Amiga-Space as well as Left Amiga-
   Space (as in V4).

d) Split At Cursor (Block menu) updates the current block number correctly.

e) Delete Last now decreases the appropriate playseq numbers correctly.

f) Sample List editor cured:

    * After adding a directory, it's selected correctly. (Also in V4)

    * Save Ins/Save All Insts no longer duplicates the instrument name if
      it already exists in the list.

g) Shift-clicking Space when Space is on now keeps Space on.

h) The print header has had another clean-up:

    * The section numbers are printed correctly (they used to be printed
      one less then their correct value).

    * No extra linefeed is printed after the relative volumes.

i) Saving songs with more than 256 blocks no longer gurus! (#8000 000B).

j) Sample Editor: Play Buffer Contents displays "Copy buffer empty." if the
   buffer is empty.

k) Clicking Digitize when Buffsize = 0 allocates a buffer automatically
   (131072 bytes or (if no memory) the largest size available).

l) Sample Editor: Clicking <Sample now changes the volume to 64 if the slot
   is empty.
@ENDNODE


@NODE o_v500e "OctaMED Professional V5.00e"
** OctaMED Professional V5.00e (29th Aug 1993) ***Copyright RBF Software***


    * The status of the Save Instruments flag will remain during
      subsequent openings of the Save Options window.

    * Alternative keypad mappings and H->B are now the default
      settings (if no config file exists).

    * "Couldn't load MED_Paths" removed.

    * Synth Editor Waveform integer gadget fixed.

    * Block list (and Section list) positioning perfected.

    * Flushing the instrument clears the Range gadgets in sample
      editor.

    * SList Editor Pitch box bug fixed.

    * Transpose/Finetune slider 3 pixels longer ;-)

    * The About requester shows the compilation date (my own idea,
      surprisingly), for those that write about problems.
      You can now tell me the date your copy was compiled. (please).

@ENDNODE


@NODE o_v500f "OctaMED Professional V5.00f"
** OctaMED Professional V5.00f (10-10-93) ***Copyright RBF Software***

(This is the version you are using now!)

    * Sample Editor loop gadget fixed

    * Left-Amiga-Del works again!

    * Don't advance + spacing work now together.

    * After digitizing, the inst. default vol is set to 64 (if it's zero)

    * H->B works by default, if no config file.

    * Input map scroller position bug fixed

    * Sample list Stats requester clearer.

    * Fixed a few bugs in the PD OctaMEDPlayer. (now works with V1.3 os)

@ENDNODE

